text.section:
The administrative regulations promulgated by the board shall also address:
The location and housing of beauty salons or cosmetology schools in the state. To this end, the board may make reasonable divisions and subdivisions of the state. This subsection does not apply to the instructional programs in cosmetology in the state area vocational and technical schools;
The quantity and quality of equipment, supplies, materials, records, and furnishings required in beauty salons, nail salons, or cosmetology schools;
The training and supervision of cosmetology apprentices;
The qualifications of teachers of cosmetology and apprentice teachers of cosmetology;
The hours and courses of instruction at cosmetology schools;
The examinations of applicants for licenses;
The proper education and training of students; and
The course and conduct of school owners, instructors, apprentice instructors, licensed cosmetologists, nail technicians, beauty salons, nail salons, and cosmetology schools.
